description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title – Staff Nurse – Band 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base – Stroud Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary – £24,907 to £30,615 per annum pro rata&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours per week – 25&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for a Registered Practitioner to join our team. We are seeking an experienced Endoscopy Practitioner who is looking for the challenge of working in a dedicated, caring and motivated team in our JAG accredited Unit. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The successful applicant will have post registration experience in endoscopy, with the range of skills required to work in all areas of the service and support the existing team. Experience is required in admission, discharge, airway management, accessories/biopsies, and decontamination. A sound knowledge of JAG processes, GRS requirements and JET training is essential for this position. We welcome those who are looking for a unit that is supportive and innovative.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are passionate about the quality of our endoscopy services and pride ourselves on clinical &amp; nursing leadership. We deliver care/services of the highest quality to our local communities and we are proud that our patient, family and friends feedback is outstanding. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stroud is a beautiful market town in a semi-rural position that has the added bonus of being in close proximity to the M5 motorway and is also serviced by excellent train links to London, Bristol and the South West; our site offers free parking. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The post provides excellent opportunities for professional development within the countywide endoscopy services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For informal enquiries/informal visits please contact Severine Ryder 0300 421 8944 severine.ryder@ghc,nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The qualification, training &amp; experience requirements for the role are underlined in the Job Description/Person Specification.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 16th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shortlisting date: 17th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust aims to recruit and retain the best possible staff who, through the application of their skills, qualification and experience, will make a positive contribution to our business of providing quality health care services. It is the Trust’s view that the costs associated with moving house in order to take up a post with us should not restrict our ability to recruit the excellent people we need, therefore we support staff to relocate with our relocation policy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post requires the post holder to be able to undertake all statutory and mandatory training and post holders must be able to undertake physical interventions. Fitness for physical intervention will be assessed by Occupational Health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A valid UK driving licence plus the use of own transport for business purposes is essential. For qualifying staff the Trust has a Lease Car Scheme in place and also offers a popular Salary Sacrifice Car Scheme with our partner Tusker.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To ensure you fully understand how the Trust, as a Data Controller, will process and store your data please read the attached document ‘ Applicant and Staff Privacy Notice’ prior to applying for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates for any staff appointment shall, when making application, disclose in writing to the Trust whether they are related to any governor. Failure to disclose such a relationship may disqualify a candidate and, if appointed, may render him/her liable to dismissal.&lt;/p&gt;
